race.comment: Tough. MOSGIEL DAISY (3) was well in commission last time but ran below expectations, beaten 2 lengths over 1609m at this track. Impressed winning this grade and distance at Kempsey prior and deserves another chance. GOLDEN HONOUR (2) comes out of the same race here and missed a whisker from the front. Dropping back 200m shouldn't bother, and fourth-up she's a chance to go one better. FOX REIGN (8) was well supported in that contest and was plain (slow to recover). The Kempsey near miss prior stacks up, and all must be in order. WILDERNESS STAR (12) has won here twice before and draws for a soft run so could play a role.
